<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>93470</id>
    <title>Crash when using File -&gt; Open or Cmd+O to open file as first interaction (OSX 10.10.5)</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">I am running LO 5.0.0.5 on OS X 10.10.5.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.2">LO crashes if I open it to the start center and then press Cmd+O or use File -&gt; Open from the menu BEFORE doing anything else.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">Steps to reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">1 Open LibreOffice from the LibreOffice.app icon.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">The start center opens.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.4">2a.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.5">WITHOUT clicking on anything or defocusing the window, press Cmd+O to open a file.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.6">2b.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.7">OR choose File -&gt; Open from the menu.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.8">3 A dialog saying "LibreOffice 5.0 - Fatal Error" and "Given module is not a frame nor a window, controller or model."</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.9">opens.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.10">When you close the dialog, LO closes.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">Expected behaviour:</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.2">LO should open the file dialog and allow me to open a file.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">If I click on any part of the UI or defocus and refocus the window, Cmd+O and File -&gt; Open work normally.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">I could not find a similar bug with search.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
